				</div>
		  
					<div class="comment-body">
						
			
						<p>Agreed, Felicity is NOT making macaroons! And she has made a rather good effort for a novice! <br>As lucymutch says, the rapping on the counter and the resting to create a skin, will make a successful finish.<br>As with all things meringue, humid conditions can be a muck up.</p><p>A tip: if using parchment paper, when your macaroons are finished baking, quickly raise one end of the parchment and spray a bit of water on the baking sheet. <br>The steam created will allow the creations to lift off the sheets with minimum breakage.</p>
						
